caption: Amazing fresh Cambodian food - it's delicious and inexpensive! I had the Ba Bong which is a vermicelli noodle bowl with beef and vegetables and a homemade dressing, it also comes with a crispy egg roll. My friend had the beef lo lac which is stir fry beef with rice and a different but equally tasty homemade dressing. I highly recommend both dishes! Everything tasted homemade and comes with tips on how to enjoy it the best way. We placed an order for pickup; it was quick, clean and efficient. If you haven't been to this little gem, definitely try it (especially the egg rolls)!
Amazing customer service and genuine care. The food was amazing and the experience of eating there made it better.

My favorite order: Beef Skewers w/ rice and extra slaw + spring rolls + Thai Tea - YUMMMM! The beef is marinated to the heavens that you can taste in every sweet and savory bite, making it my absolute fave. Paired with their homemade slaw and house sauce? LOVE! Topping it off with a refreshing Thai Tea with boba.
Fantastic Dinner! Everything was fresh made to order. If you get a chance to go. Go! Highly recommended.
Always quality. Good folks
Food was super good. But the service was actually amazing. They’re such nice people and really cared to make sure you enjoyed the food.

Best chicken of my life! I'm serious, I got the Chicken Skewers a couple times and they never fail-- tender, juicy, flavorful. Never over-cooked or dry! I highly recommend this place. Friendly service and the owner seems like such a wonderful person! My brother ordered the Beef Skewers and had equally rave reviews. The house-made chili oil is bomb, if you like spice make sure you try it. Great egg rolls and the Mango Sticky Rice was excellent.

Polite staff , and beyond reasonable I had an entree I tried out just too try new things and turns out I'm not a soup person but one of the staff took the entree I didn't like off my bill and I got something else . I encourage anyone too go here for the amazing flavors and great staff

Although the owners are from Cambodia and it is marketed as a Cambodian restaurant, the food is quite similar to Thai & Vietnamese food. Compared to most Thai or Vietnamese restaurant menus, the menu here is more limited, but there's enough to choose from to satisfy most people.  The food was very tasty, and everyone I was eating with ate everything on their plate. Additionally, afterwards the chef / owner came out to our table, introduced themself, and asked if we were happy with our meal. We got into a short conversation with him, and he was super friendly and nice.  My only (small) complaint is that they don't really allow customers to request that the food be made hotter (by adding more chili or spices) or less salty or sweet--the chef has a recipe and sticks to it.  That said, the food was very good, and the staff and owners were much friendlier than found at the average restaurant. Support local small business owners--eat at Prum's Kitchen!!

We chose to have dinner at Prum’s Kitchen because of the high reviews, and we are so glad we did!  It’s a small, unassuming restaurant, but our meals were exquisitely prepared and extremely flavorful!  The service was welcoming and attentive and  Bo Prum was a wonderful host!  We will definitely return!!  Highly recommend this restaurant!!
Delicious food and very nice service.

This was my first time having Cambodian food and it was so delicious! The food was fresh and flavorful! I work downtown so I was able to walk to the location to pick up my order. The staff were so friendly and helpful. I also appreciated the order being in a recyclable container. I cannot wait to go back a try other dishes!

Thanks to all the other reviewers for steering us here. Don't let the spartan atmosphere fool you, this place makes awesome food. Best egg rolls I've ever had, and they're the only thing there made in advance. Everything else is made fresh to order. The owners are gracious hosts and go out of their way for their guests. Excellent in every way.

My favorite order: Beef Skewers w/ rice and extra slaw + spring rolls + Thai Tea - YUMMMM! The beef is marinated to the heavens that you can taste in every sweet and savory bite, making it my absolute fave. Paired with their homemade slaw and house sauce? LOVE! Topping it off with a refreshing Thai Tea with boba.
Absolutely charming and thoughtful service! Everything was delicious and cooked exactly to order. And they have outdoor seating with a heater! Can't wait to come back again.
Very kind and really good food.

I ordered the chicken skewer entree for take out. I must say my chicken was not fully cooked which is such a shame given that they didn’t have to rush to complete this order. Maybe appropriately measure the cooking temperature next time.  Edit: changed from three to five stars. Very nice customer service from the owner. I thank them for their offer. Please, if you see a person in need, give that meal to them. Much appreciated! I really like their menu and will be reordering! I will ask for slightly more well done chicken if I order again, but everything else was very tasty. Especially loved their tofu.
I forgot to take pics. The food was tasty. The service was great and the atmosphere was inviting.
excellent prices for the quality, and the best service, easy to eat here very day.
Lovely people and delicious southeast Asian food. What a hidden gem in north Florida!
So delicious and such friendly attentive staff!! The portions were nice and big as well. Definitely recommend trying it out!
Great food at a reasonable price, Prum and the crew provide great service as well!
Omg omg . Heaven in a plate .
Delishes food, friendly service, I'll be back!
Food is healthy and taste just fine. Prices are good too.
My third time this week, too good..
Food was excellent, boba tea was delicious, big portions and I'm a hungry man so I dont play, good prices, and great customer service

Please support this business so they can stay open. The broth is very flavorful and everything is fresh and delicious. They have the best food I have ever had in my life! Their Cambodian noodles are my new comfort food. The difficulty finding parking isn't their fault. The city closed off all the parking around the block so now these businesses have less people coming in :(
Great 👌. Food was fantastic
Good quality of food at best price. Pocket friendly Foodie restaurant. Awesome customer services and well professional staff👌
Great service as well as great food.

Solid flavors (at a price)  Overall, this restaurant tastes similar to most Thai restaurants I’ve eaten at. Flavors are solid, but they have a limited menu for vegetarian.  Ended up paying about $20 including tax for a rice dish with tofu, boba tea, and mango sticky rice.

Prum’s Kitchen has such a wonderful homely environment. I’ve been visiting PK since they opened up and so far the service has always been top notch. The Beef Loc Lac here is really amazing! PK was my first introduction to Cambodian food and culture. Wonderful addition to GNV!  **UPDATE** By now I've been eating here atleast 3 times a month for the last 7 months or so. The food is consistently top notch (I always end up eating the beef loc lac). Leanna and Bo Prum are wonderful human beings and they take good care of their patrons. As someone who is still fairly new to Gainesville and many many miles away from home, Prum's Kitchen is one of those lovely spots that makes Gainesville home for me!
Mr. Prum gave us amazing service, great food! Go for the meat skewers, super tasty! Had the Ba Bong but didn't realize it was a mixed temperature dish so probably will order more meat next time.

We are so happy to have stumbled upon this restaurant!! The food is delicious and the ingredients are soo fresh. I had the Ba-Bong and my husband had the Shrimp Fried Rice. We both couldn't stop saying “mmm” with each bite! We will be back with friends. :)
The food was delicious and the owner was so nice! I would definitely recommend!
The food was all very refreshing and filling, but it didn't really wow me as it was not very flavorful. Worth checking out but with tempered expectations.

Excellent
Amazing skewers. i dined in and the service was outstanding

Prum's Kitchen offers delicious meals with flavor profiles unlike any I've had in Gainesville. The meal I had was a perfect blend of sweet, sour, and savory with a little bit of spice. I appreciate their simple menu because I often have a hard time deciding when I go to a new restaurant. I ordered the Ba Bong entree and Salt & Pepper wings appetizer, and my roommate ordered the Loc Lac entree, all of these were delicious. Our service was exceptional, and the server and owner checked on us multiple times to make sure we were satisfied and had everything we needed. The owner Bo also spoke to us after we ate and was happy to explain the flavors in our dishes. Thank you to the Prum family for this wonderful introduction to Cambodian food!
Very good food!  I recommend the Ba-Bong!  The egg rolls also taste good.  I will continue to eat food from here.
Everyone was really respectful and nice and the food came out really quickly! You should definitely try the skewers! The Ba-Bong was really good but the skewers really stood out.

The Beef Ba-Bong is impressive great and brought me right back to Guangzhou,China!I couldn’t help but asking for en extra beef topping . We were there late last night but the service is really friendly and the chef is super nice! It beats all the Vietnamese noodles bowls in Palm Beach country,Florida!!! First highlight of our culinary vacation! We ate them all before we remember to take pictures lol.

We stopped here after 9pm and was blown away by the food and kind service.  I enjoyed the beef Ba Bong bowl.  The noodles were delicious and complemented by fresh tasty vegetables. And the staff was nice and came to check on us often.  Thanks again!
Always well prepared and delicious. Always a delight to interact with everyone who works here. When in doubt, order the Ba-Bong (beef or vegetable; you'll be satisfied either way) 😋😍
Amazing food Wonderful owners. Cambodian food that’s absolutely perfectly made and service was top notch.

I highly recommend this place.  The food is Amazing and the service is outstanding. Very worth  the trip downtown. I had the chef’s special and wings and rolls.  The family that runs this place is very pleasant.
Authentic and delicious. Best chicken I’ve had in a very long time. Highly recommend this place
Very good!!! I highly recommend!! Nice place too.
Delicious!  The whole family enjoyed everything we got.   Definitely recommend the Phnom Penh Noodles.
Order mango sticky rice 😋
I went to Prum for lunch today and the service was incredible and I loved the beef dish that I got! Great experience!

We enjoyed the shrimp fried rice and the beef skewers.  Very tasty, the skewers were delicious, tender and flavorful. We enjoyed speaking with Bo, the owner.  Very nice family run business.  We will return when we visit our son, who is attending UF.

The food was awesome, and the customer service is amazing! I'll definitely be returning here in the future. I accidentally dropped the broth for one of the entries in the parking lot, and they replaced it for me. So polite and understanding!
Very good food. It's light and refreshing, perfect Florida weather food.
We went there last night and everything was phenomenal. The service is exceptional, and the shrimp fried rice is a must have! I'm looking forward to going back.

We got delivery from here and really liked their Ba Bong bowl, but nothing in particular stood out and took it to the next level. It's very similar to the Vietnamese vermicelli noodle bowls. Huge portions for a very reasonable price. Delivery was relatively fast. Looking forward to trying more things soon!  Edit: Highly recommend the skewers!

Had lunch here today & all I can say is YUM! Food was awesome, fresh, plated beautifully, oh so good. The chicken & beef skewers were so tasty, & the beef just melted in your mouth,  the soup to die for. Not to mention Bo & Leanne, the owners, are the sweetest people on the planet. I can’t wait to go back, highly recommend this restaurant. The portions are huge,. I was to full for dessert but got a sticky rice with mango to bring home. Oh my goodness it is delish! The place is tastefully, no pun intended, decorated & so cute. If you like Cambodian food this is the place. So glad they are here in Gainesville. I would give it not just five stars but ten!!!
Had the ba bong for take out and it was great. They even put a guide on how to use the sauces properly on the take out boxes!!
Delicious!! Everything was so flavorful and cooked perfectly! Egg rolls to die for!

I wasn’t planning on buying takeout tonight, but I made the decision on a whim because I didn’t feel like cooking and was meaning to try this place out. I got two entrées: Ba Bong and the Chicken Skewers (came with rice and salad).  I am SOOO IMPRESSED!! I almost finished the Ba Bong and started eating the skewers already!! (This was supposed to last me until tomorrow evening. :( )  Ba Bong: juicy stir fried beef, FRESH vegetables (lettuce, bean sprouts, carrots and cucumbers), and the egg rolls that it comes with were sooo tasty and freshly fried!  Chicken Skewers entrée: rice was so fresh!, the marinade for the marinated mini salad was also good (has ginger, by the way!) and is a good palate cleanser; chicken was grilled perfectly, flavorful and moist!  For dessert, I split the mango sticky rice with my roommate: perfect amount of sugar <3, the mango was so RIPE!!!, the rice—indeed sticky! Haha  Now, for the atmosphere:  The decor is beautiful and reflects part of the Khmer culture (mostly the intricate paintings!).  The owners and other employees are so sweet!! and able to kindly and patiently answer any inquiries about menu items. They are clearly invested in the restaurant and in their customers.  The restaurant itself is SO clean and looks well maintained.  The prices are good for the quality and quantity of food.  Overall my first experience purchasing takeout from Prum’s kitchen left me completely satisfied. :) I definitely recommend!
Great service, delicious food!

Fantastic pickup order at Prum’s Kitchen tonight. We have been wanting to dine at Prum’s when they first opened months ago In Gainesville but time got away from us until today. Tonight, due to virus, we ordered curbside and picked up a family order to enjoy at home.  When we called in our order we received wonderful advice on which items to order as we we’re unaccustomed to Cambodian  cuisine.  We have only ordered take away foods twice in the  past 8 weeks but our next order will be with Prum’s Kitchen again.  Well Done, Prum’s We certainly enjoyed our meal !

Nice venue, great location for downtown dining. We arrived at peak lunch time and were seated immediately.  Unfortunately we then waited over an hour for the food. This of course required us to go add quarters to the meter. The food was good.  It was similar to Vietnamese that I have had in the past.  However, it wasn't 'go out of your way'  good. He did apologize for the wait.

Phnom Penh noodle meal is the equivalent of "Vietnamese Pho" courtesy of this fresh Ma & Pa restaurant in the heart of downtown Gainsville. Im pretty sure this place is the only one like it for miles around. Go easy when dealing with Bo and his wife, who prepares the dishes in the kitchen. They are very kind and extremely polite, be sure to be nice to them both.
Delicious and the owners are wonderful people.
Great food and family owned, friendly atmosphere.  Simple menu that covers everything you'd want!
This place is so cozy and the food tastes like authentic food! It’s very similar to Vietnamese food in a way. Super flavorful Im surprised I’ve never seen this place before
Excellent! Great food, prices, and service
Best authentic Cambodian food in town! You have to try it!!!!
Great food and friendly staff. Made good use of the small space.  Recommend the skewers.

This place just opened up, so I'm being a little lenient in my review.  I was really excited for Cambodian food, because I've never had it before. I assumed it would have similarities to Vietnamese or Thai, but when I heard authentic Cambodian food, you know I was expecting some real Asian stuff. Funky stuff, you know? Well, the food pretty good, but pretty basic in terms of flavor profile.  I ordered the beef skewers, ba-bong, and crispy egg rolls. The beef skewers tasted great, and I thought the ba-bong was decent, not great. Overall, it seemed like stuff I could have gone to any of our local Vietnamese restaurants and ordered. The prices would have been cheaper there. Also, unlike the Vietnamese resturants who have like 30 items, this place has 4 items. Usually, this might be a selling point, but kind of disappointing when they are things I could get elsewhere.  I will say the boba ice tea (basically Thai tea with boba) and the boba iced coffee (similar, if not the same as iced Vietnamese coffee) was great, but i guess I've never had bad Thai tea.  I guess if there's one thing I had to say, it would be: while the food is decent, if I hadn't known it was a Cambodian restaurant, I would have assumed it was an overpriced Vietnamese one.
Delicious food and friendly staff. Highly recommend it!
Excellent food. Still working out the kinks of opening.
Decent for take out, not so much for dinning in.
